    rectoEn: '"Long and variable lags": transmission delays — how long, and what consequence for steering?',
    versoEn: 'Transmission takes 12 TO 18 MONTHS to bite fully: already-signed loans keep running, launched projects get finished, wages renegotiate on fixed dates. Consequence: the central bank STEERS THROUGH THE REAR-VIEW MIRROR — today\'s published inflation is the product of decisions taken a year and a half ago. Hence the recurring "pause" debate: tightening until inflation visibly falls mechanically guarantees one brake stroke too many. The right question: what will TODAY\'S decisions produce by the end of next year?',
