    rectoEn: 'The panel: "The wealth effect: why is the asset-price channel strong in the US and weak in Europe?"',
    versoEn: 'Reflex: because household wealth is not invested the same way. In the US, retirement lives in the stock market (401k, brokerage accounts): when equities drop 20%, the median household feels poorer and spends less — the channel bites. In Europe, savings sleep in property, savings accounts and euro-denominated life insurance: the stock market can fall without touching most people\'s sense of wealth. Same channel, different calibre — a textbook case of transmission depending on the STRUCTURE of the economy, not just the rate.',
