    versoEn: 'Term by term: 2 + 0.5 = 2.5; inflation gap −1.5, half = −0.75 → 1.75; gap −6, half = −3 → −1.25%. The rule prescribes a NEGATIVE rate — impossible: 0% banknotes drain deposits first. One-sentence conclusion: "when Taylor prescribes −1.25% and the zero bound blocks at 0, you need another tool acting on long rates — the birth certificate of QE". The calculation and its conclusion count together: either alone is incomplete.',
