    versoEn: '(300 − 180)/60 = +2σ — in thousands, the zeros cancel. Translation: a two-standard-deviation surprise happens only ~2% of the time — rare hence violent; hawkish on employment, so BAD for bonds (higher rate path → selling → long yields up) and, in an inflation-dominant regime, bad for equities too. Training variant: actual 260, consensus 180, sigma 40 → the same +2σ with a smaller raw gap — sigma sets the scale, not the thousands of jobs.',
