    rectoEn: 'The universal reading grid for a rate shock: why is "everything a discounted cash flow"?',
    versoEn: 'Every asset is worth the sum of its discounted future flows — and the rate sits IN THE DENOMINATOR: when the central bank raises it, every numerator in the world reprices. Bonds: EXACT transmission through duration. Equities: distant flows suffer more — growth has long duration. Credit: double blow, rate plus spread. FX: rate differentials, capital flows. Gold: zero flows — its "rate" is an opportunity cost, the real rate. One grid, five variations: the chapter\'s map.',
