    rectoEn: 'Gold under the monetary cycle: what is its true thermometer — and why not inflation?',
    versoEn: 'Gold has NO CASH FLOW: no coupon, no dividend — holding it costs what the risk-free asset would pay, once inflation is deducted: its thermometer is the REAL RATE. Negative real rate: holding gold is "free", it rises. Rising real rate: the opportunity cost reappears, gold suffers. Proof by 2022: 9% inflation — gold\'s paradise, one thought — and gold ends FLAT, because the real rate went from −1 to +1.5%. The line that sticks: inflation proposes, the real rate disposes.',
