    rectoEn: 'The equity-bond correlation: what determines its sign — and why is it vital for a 60/40 portfolio?',
    versoEn: 'The INFLATION REGIME. Inflation under control: dominant shocks are growth shocks — bad economic news = equities down but rates down too (easing expectations) = bonds up: NEGATIVE correlation, the bond insures the equity. Inflation dominant: the shock is the rate itself — it hits BOTH legs at once: POSITIVE correlation. 2022: the US 60/40 ~−17%, worst year since 2008 — the insurance failed exactly when needed. Diversification is not a physical constant: it is a regime variable.',
