    rectoEn: 'The common grammar of the 2013, 2022 and 2023 accidents (taper tantrum, gilts/LDI, SVB)?',
    versoEn: 'Three ingredients every time: 1) DURATION accumulated through the low-rate years — it is everywhere: bond portfolios, pension-fund hedges, bank balance sheets; 2) LEVERAGE or fragile funding — margined LDI hedges, sight deposits funding 10-year securities; 3) a fast RATE SHOCK that turns the latent loss into a MARGIN CALL or a withdrawal — and the solvent position into a forced sale. Duration measures the risk; liquidity materialises it; margin turns the latent loss into a spiral.',
