    rectoEn: 'The exact transmission of a rate shock to bonds — the formula, its conventions, and the two canonical applications?',
    versoEn: '$\\dfrac{\\Delta P}{P} \\approx -D_{\\text{mod}} \\times \\Delta y$ — $\\Delta y$ in basis points, answer in % ($D$ = module 4\'s modified duration). Canonical applications: $+100$ bp on duration 7: $-7\\ \\%$; $+300$ bp on duration 8: $-24\\ \\%$ — that is 2022, and the Global Agg at $-17\\ \\%$. Oral nuances: a LINEAR approximation, pessimistic for the holder (convexity softens); and duration is MAXIMAL when coupons are zero — starting from zero rates means taking the shock with no cushion.',
